It was with this newfound ability that Albino confronted Allen Kane, hoping to subdue him through sensorial means rather than physical confrontation. He focused, attempting to envelop Kane in the suffocating grip of fear. However, to Albino's consternation, Kane remained unaffected, his posture unyielding, his resolve unwavering. This immunity to the fear assault provided irrefutable proof of Kane's Heruka nature. 

Only a Heruka, with their unique neural constitution and adaptive physiology, could stand immune to the effects of each otherâ€™s abilities. It explained the failure of the Death Touch; Kane's anatomy was fundamentally altered, rendering him impervious to such targeted neural disruptions.

